data.Name: Percussion
data.Description: A hollow, retrievable, cylindrical bullet is shot into the borehole wall and retrieved with the rock sample inside.

data.Name: Rotary
data.Description: A diamond-tipped drill cuts a plug from the borehole wall. The drill and sample are retracted into the body of the tool.

data.Name: Percussion sidewall core
data.Description: DEPRECATED: Please use Code="Percussion" with Name="Percussion" instead. Cylindrical sidewall core acquired using a wireline logging tool.  Cores are explosively cut and thus generally more damaged.  Cores are typically up to 4.5cm long and 2.5cm wide.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Rotary sidewall core
data.Description: DEPRECATED: Please use Code="Rotary" with Name="Rotary" instead. Cylindrical sidewall core acquired using a wireline logging tool.  Cores are mechanically extracted and thus generally less damaged.  Cores are typically up to 5cm long and 2.5cm wide.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).
